### prompt
Write a function called make_sentence that takes an array of strings (words) as an argument and returns the string created by concatenating all the words with spaces in between.

### solution
function make_sentence(words) {
  return words.join(' ');
}

### test
var ll = {{ x }};
for (var i = 0; i < ll.length; i++)
  console.log(make_sentence(ll[i]));

### hint
Here's code for the make_csv function which takes array of strings as an argument
and returns the string created by concatenating all the strings with commas in
between:
<pre>
function make_csv(array) {
  return array.join(',');
}
</pre>

